## Task 4 Directory and File Enumeration

Objective: Use Gobuster in dir mode to discover directories and files.
Gobuster’s dir mode brute forces directory structures using wordlists.
Useful in penetration testing to reveal hidden paths (e.g., WordPress: /wp-admin, /wp-content, /wp-includes).
Returns HTTP status codes to indicate accessibility.
Flags:
- -c / --cookies → pass session cookies.
- -x / --extensions → specify file extensions (.php, .js).
- -H / --headers → add custom headers.
- -k / --no-tls-validation → skip TLS checks.
- -n / --no-status → hide status codes.
- -P / --password + -U / --username → authenticated requests.
- -s / --status-codes → show specific codes.
- -b / --status-codes-blacklist → hide unwanted codes.
- -r / --followredirect → follow HTTP redirects.
Examples:
Code
- gobuster dir -u http://www.example.thm -w /usr/share/wordlists/dirbuster/directory-list-2.3-medium.txt -r
Code
- gobuster dir -u http://www.example.thm -w /usr/share/wordlists/dirbuster/directory-list-2.3-medium.txt -x .php,.js

