## Task 5 Subdomain Enumeration

Objective: Use Gobuster in dns mode to discover subdomains.
Subdomains may contain vulnerabilities not present in the main domain.
Example: tryhackme.thm vs. mobile.tryhackme.thm.
Flags:
- -c / --show-cname → display CNAME records.
- -i / --show-ips → show resolved IP addresses.
- -r / --resolver → specify custom DNS server.
- -d / --domain → target domain.
Example:
Code
- gobuster dns -d example.thm -w /usr/share/wordlists/SecLists/Discovery/DNS/subdomains-top1million-5000.txt
Sample output:
- Found: www.example.thm
- Found: shop.example.thm
- Found: academy.example.thm
- Found: primary.example.thm

---

## Task 6 Virtual Host Enumeration

Objective: Use Gobuster in vhost mode to discover virtual hosts.
Virtual hosts = multiple websites hosted on the same server/IP.
Difference vs. subdomains:
- DNS mode → queries DNS records (-d flag).
- Vhost mode → brute forces hostnames via HTTP requests (-u flag).
Flags:
- -u / --url → base URL.
- --append-domain → appends base domain to wordlist entries.
- -m / --method → HTTP method.
- --domain → sets domain appended to wordlist entries.
- --exclude-length → filters responses by body length.
- -r / --follow-redirect → follows HTTP redirects.
Example:
Code
gobuster vhost -u http://MACHINE_IP --domain example.thm -w /usr/share/wordlists/SecLists/Discovery/DNS/subdomains-top1million-5000.txt --append-domain --exclude-length 250-320
Sample output:
- Found: blog.example.thm → Status 200
- Found: shop.example.thm → Status 200
- Found: academy.example.thm → Status 200
- False positives filtered by --exclude-length.

